Project: Solo Houses by Makoto Takei + Chie Nabeshima (TNA)

design for solo houses appears as an upside down concrete pyramid that has been partially sunken into the rural terrain. large apertures provide the home with daylight and ventilation, while internal living spaces are organized around a series of mezzanines or platforms, set at different heights. .
.

node.text:
Who knows this house?

#hemeroscopiumhouse @debora_ensamble @anton_ensamble #madrid

Captured by  @iwanbaan

The place where the sun sets is known as Hemeroscopium. An reference to a realm that only exists in our minds, in our senses, that is ever-changing and malleable but nonetheless real. It is determined by the horizon's references, by the physical limitations set by light, and it occurs in time.

A new amazing language is created, in which form vanishes and the naked space takes its place. Hemeroscopium House reaches the pinnacle of its balance with the "G point," a twenty-ton granite stone that expresses gravity and serves as a physical counterweight to the entire structure, as they call it at Ensamble Studio. 

👇 Follow @architecture.c for more !
